    "patient_text_brief": "[MAIN PROBLEM]\n- My baby's eyes and face look yellow.\n- It is NOT on his chest, belly, arms, or legs.\n- It started slowly about 4 weeks ago.\n- It was worse at 2 weeks, but looks a bit better now.\n\n[OTHER SYMPTOMS]\n- No fever.\n- No vomiting.\n- He feeds very well (breastmilk only).\n- His poop is normal yellow color.\n- His pee is normal clear/pale.\n- No cold, cough, or trouble breathing.\n\n[HISTORY]\n- Born on time (full term).\n- Normal delivery, no ICU stay.\n- I only breastfeed him, nothing else.\n- I have never stopped breastfeeding him.\n- No medicines given.\n- No other health problems.",
